result.title: How to avoid wrong answer on pre-tests?
result.content: Can anyone suggest me how to get out from this "Wrong answer on pre-test N" cycle? It seems that in all the rounds that I have participated, I have always gotten wrong answers in the pre-tests.. usually pre-test 10,11 etc. Although the sample input gives the correct output... could anyone suggest me how to practise in order to improve and get wong answer on pre-tests less often?
